	<key>readme</key>
	<string># alfred-emoji

![icon](images/icon.png)

An Alfred workflow that makes it easy to
search for emoji and copy them to the clipboard 🤘.

## Installing

On first run the workflow downloads emoji data and generates icons automatically.

A progress indicator shows in Alfred while this is happening — results appear
once setup is complete.

![install](images/install.png)

## Usage

```
emoji [query]
```

* ↵ (return) - Copy the emoji symbol (e.g. 🤣) to the clipboard
* ⌥↵ (alt + return) - Copy the emoji code (e.g. `:rofl:`) to the clipboard
* ⌃↵ (ctrl + return) - Copy the codepoint (e.g. `U+1F923`) to the clipboard
* ⇧↵ (shift + return) - Copy the base symbol without skin tone modifier

### Hotkey and snippet triggers

You can also trigger the workflow without typing the `emo` keyword:

- **Hotkey** — bind a keyboard shortcut in Alfred preferences. Activates the
  search directly, same as typing the keyword.
- **Snippet** — configure a text snippet shortcut in Alfred preferences. When
  triggered this way, pressing ↵ **pastes** the emoji directly into the
  frontmost application instead of copying it to the clipboard (same as the
  command modifier when using hotkey/keyword.

### Skin tone

Set the `skin_tone` workflow variable in the combo box to the left.

The ⇧ modifier always copies the base symbol regardless of the skin tone setting.

## Automatic Updates

The workflow checks for new releases once weekly and installs them
automatically. All downloads come directly from official GitHub Releases.

Emoji data kept up to date: the workflow checks for upstream changes to
[emojilib](https://github.com/muan/emojilib) and [unicode-emoji-json](https://github.com/muan/unicode-emoji-json)
 weekly and regenerates icons when new emoji are published.

